commitResults.messageTitle: Add functions for introductory message and dividers
Added function to print user's command till a terminating command is received. Also added comments for functions.
Added function to add and list tasks
- Added Class: [Task] This is to keep track of the task status and its description.
commitResults.messageBody: - Updated taskList (arraylist) to contain Task instead of String

commitResults.messageTitle: Added the ability to update the status of task (done / not done).
Added Text UI Testing. Also modify the shell script to ignore whitespace as there seems to be an issue comparing tab spacing.
This commit contain the following updates:
commitResults.messageBody:
1) Added 3 different types of Task:
- ToDos
- Deadlines
- Events
All are classes that extends the primary <Task> class. With these, users can now add 3 different type of task in his list.

2) Added a InvalidTaskInputException class
This will be used to handle events whereby no date is specified by the user for <Deadlines> and <Events>

3) Slight refactoring of codes to consolidate:
- <determineAction> to know what is the command input by user
- <getTaskDetails> to get a string containing the full details of a task.

commitResults.messageTitle: Added <UnknownCommandInputException> exception class to catch unknown inputs given by user.
Added ability to delete task in task list.
Perform code refactoring by: 1) Organise all files to be under "com.calebjianhui.duke". 2) Move all UI related matters to a separate package "ui"

These update includes: 1) Perform more OOP by segregating the code to their respective packages based on their relevant functions (commands, enums, parser, taskmanager, ui) 2) Removal of exception packages as it is not best practice to have its own package, instead it is placed in the relevant packages that calls it.
Added functions: - Saving of tasks to file upon every update - Loading of tasks from file at start of program
commitResults.messageBody: Several refactoring was done with respect to adding of these new functions.
